==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frap
<hw>Frap</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Frapped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Frapping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>frapper</ets> to
strike, to seize ropes. Cf. <er>Affrap</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To draw together; to bind with a view to secure
and strengthen, as a vessel by passing cables around it; to tighten; as
a tackle by drawing the lines together.</def>
<rj><au>Tottem.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To brace by drawing together, as the cords of a
drum.</def> <rj><au>Knoght.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frape</ent>⟦br⟧
